<title>NETHERLANDS: Santer promises Blair fairness on BA/AA probe.</title>
<headline>Santer promises Blair fairness on BA/AA probe.</headline>
<dateline>NOORDWIJK, Netherlands 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>European Commission President Jacques Santer told British Prime Minister Tony Blair on Friday a Commission probe into the British Airways/American Airline alliance would be conducted objectively, Santer's spokesman said.</p>
<p>Nikolaus van der Pas said Blair had raised the Commission's probe in a meeting with Santer. &quot;All airline alliances will be dealt with in the same way,&quot; he quoted Santer as telling the British premier.</p>
<p>The spokesman said Blair appeared satiSfied with the comment.</p>
